When we launch in the future, we will have mugs for you, our queens. For now, here are a few things you need to know about mugs. mugs can be used for more that simply drinking coffee.

üå∏ 1. Sharpen Knives: You can sharpen a blunt knife by rubbing it against the bottom of a cup.

üå∏ 2. Drainage Rock: a drainage rock is what allows water to be released from plants in pots, so that excess water does not remain in the plant which causes the roots to rot. If there is no way for excess water to come out then the plant can die. To make a drainage rock from a mug: put the mug under a thick cloth and crush it up with a stone, mallet or other solid material. Crush till you have small pieces, then create holes in the planting pot. Use the crushed mug to cover the holes. The crushed mugs would not let soil fall out from the pot but it would allow excess water through.

üå∏ 3. Candle: You can use mugs to hold candles, or you can even melt the entire candle wax into a coffee mug and turn it into a decorative candle itself. (Before doing this though, be sure to read all labels and be aware that some materials are flammable)

üå∏ 4. Measuring Cup: do you need to measure something and cannot find your measuring cup, then a mug is the perfect substitute. This use is pretty self-explanatory.

üå∏ 5. Cookie Cutter: if you do not have a cookie cutter, you can use mugs to cut your cookies. It should give you perfect circles.

Double tap if you like our list of other uses.

